Chairman match commissioner appointment committee of the NFF, Alhaji Babagana Kalli Kachalla will be onÂ  international duty again in neighbouring Accra as the match commissioner Thursday, 14th November, 2019 in the Africa Cup of Nations qualifier match between Black Stars of Ghana and Bafana Bafana of South Africa in Accra, Ghana.
A true ambassador of the round leather game who has played for the country at the U-17 level in 1993, Babagana Kalli remains the first Borno indigene in the board of NFF as well as one of the youngest CAF match commissioners.
His dedication in the discharge of duties set him apart as a match commissioner of repute in the countless matches he has commissioned.

			
